pageContext.claim: “We took the money and we gave it, and we had by the way, over $100 billion left over which we put into the Treasury.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false. Through Dec. 16, 2020, the Trump tariffs have garnered about $73 billion on products from China, {according to Customs and Border Protection}. Minus the $28 billion to farmers, that leaves about $45 billion -- which, as we noted, is from U.S. taxpayers, not China.
